<br>
The level spread of the available zones no longer matches the level spread of the players.  When I went through Droga and Nurga to get my shackle, there was one person of the appropriate level in either of the dungeons.  There were at least three groups of 55-60's farming faction.  Going in for the Sleeping Ogre, the dungeon was empty.  I've met one exp group at the entrance of Dalnir in my last three trips in.  The few times that I've been in SolA I've usually seen one group in there.  I haven't been in Guk or SplitPaw in over a year, so I have no idea what the utilization of those dungeons are like, but I would be suprised if they were high.  <br>
<br>
I would like to see Verant take one or two of these low/mid-level dungeons and simply add 10 or 20 levels to each mob in there.  For the first go round, don't change anything else.  The loot and spawns can be tuned afterwards, but they can't cause the dungeons to be any less utiliized and it would give one or two more zones worth of spawns for experience gathering - whether it's solo players or groups. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uchshrcat.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ChshrCat</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://pages.prodigy.net/amblint/Images/lilflag.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/12/02 7:20:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=246.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.nonstick.com/images/animated/robinani.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Why do I want to solo?</span><hr size=1> 1. My monk is only level 23. He can get like half a blue bubble per solo kill in Paludal Caverns, taking only minor damage in the process. It took me just about an hour and a half to DING 23 from 22. That amount of XP alone is all the incentive I need to solo.<br>
<br>
2. My main is a 56 cleric. To group effectively at that level, especially as a healer, requires hours to play and weeks to level. I don't always have that much time to play. So on short days I play my monk, who can solo for a shorter period of time, and still feel like I made a significant gain.<br>
<br>
3. I'm an Iksar. I'm an evil ascetic. I'm hated by everyone. I eat foods like &quot;earthworm munch&quot;. What am I supposed to do, be the life of the party? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
4. Grouping gets tiring after a while. Sometimes you just want to be alone, ya know? <p>Galavant Greenlabel, Dwarf Cleric-56<BR>
